* The maximum number of nodes at level ‘l’ of a binary tree is (2 ** l) - 1
Level of root is 1.

* Maximum number of nodes in a binary tree of height ‘h’ is (2 ** h) – 1

* Full Binary Tree: A Binary Tree is full if every node has 0 or 2 children.
               18
           /       \
         15         30
        /  \        /  \
      40    50    100   40

* Complete Binary Tree: A Binary Tree is complete Binary Tree if all levels are completely filled except possibly the
last level and the last level has all keys as left as possible.
               18
           /       \
         15         30
        /  \        /  \
      40    50    100   40
     /  \   /
    8   7  9

* Balanced Binary Tree: A binary tree is balanced if the height of the tree is O(Log n) where n is the number of nodes.